<br>
AE+Mez is simply not the best way to approach AE.  In every case, AE+stun is better.  Stuns use less mana and they can't be &quot;broken.&quot;  They are faster casting.<br>
<br>
Every AE success I've been involved in or been told about has been with AE+stun.  And, believe me, I've tried it both ways quite extensively all through my career.  Perhaps, as you say, the run of enchanters I was able to convince to try it were just sub-par.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, I am not now, and I never was, doubting the power of AE.<br>
<br>
&quot;But I can't understand your reasoning damage/mob/mana isn't high enough&quot;<br>
<br>
216 damage / MOB / 175 mana (Circle of Force) is a damage/mob/mana ( = 1.23 d/m/m).<br>
<br>
You'll notice in previous posts that I mentioned Circle of Force, as well as Thunderclap as good pre-50 AE spells.<br>
<br>
But take, for instance, Pillar of Fire (same category as Circle of Force).  Its ratio is 0.9 d/m/m.  The point is this: if you multiply the total mana pool by the ratio, you get the damage/mob.  And on a level for level basis, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> most</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> levels (with very few exceptions) the result is low enough compared with MOB hitpoints that a wizard or two could go completely OOM on one pull of just a few MOBs.<br>
<br>
Moreover, before level 53, the absolute highest number of MOBs you can hit with any given cast is 5.  That's it.  And that's only with some PBAEs.  Circle of Force is a column spell, which targets 4 at most (column spells target at most 4 at any level--this is why you don't often hear about AE groups using Pillar of Ice {although this was my only AE spell in my first post-50 AE group}).  Use of columns requires the wizard to remove himself from the target so that he doesn't kill himself--which makes controlling aggro and positioning very difficult.<br>
<br>
To take out more than 4 or 5 at a time requires a combination of The Strategy(tm) tactics and AE.  It adds yet another level of complication to the tactic which isn't insurmountable by better-than-average players.<br>
<br>
<br>
To your example of 8+ MOBs at the 45-48 level range:<br>
<br>
Thunderclap can only hit 5 at a time (unless somehow it's <br>
been changed since three weeks ago, when I was last in an AE group).  Its ratio is 232/MOB/175 mana.  It would take <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> at least</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> 5 casts of the spell to take out 5 targets (assuming it hit every target for full every time; incidentally, since this spell has a knockback component, it is frequently resisted, and is an all-or-none spell) for the average &quot;low-blue&quot; MOB at level 45.  That's a little less than 1/2 of a &quot;non twinked&quot; wizards' mana pool at level 45.  Every group of 5 beyond this requires the same contribution in mana.  So at best on one tank of mana your group could successfully take out 10 MOBs with one wizard casting, assuming one or perhaps two resists.<br>
<br>
Moreover, mezmerisation doesn't work on stunned/forced MOBs (i.e., casting mezmerise on a stunned/forced MOB will cause it to break both--if you don't believe me, have an enchanter cast Mezmerise on a MOB after you Tishan it or use, say, Thunderstrike (level 29 force spell)).  So your claim that they were never unmezzed for more than a second is quite suspect, while being entirely possible.<br>
<br>
I don't doubt you pulled this off once on a good day.  It's entirely possible.  But it's just not something that is probable.  The numbers and mechanics of the game don't lie.  The number of &quot;happy coincidences&quot; required to pull such a thing off is just too great to try and pass off such an event as a &quot;regularity.&quot;<br>
<br>
It's almost as absurd as claiming that AE tactics aren't viable.<br>
<br>
Exaggerated claims on either end don't serve anything but to cast doubt on the whole cause, which presumably is the betterment of the class.<br>
<br>
&quot;So... before you dismiss tactics, think them through... you know kinda out of the box thinking. &quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, because we all know how novel and unique a wizard suggesting AE tactics is.  Why, you're one of the few who has ever suggested it or tried it.  Almost no other wizard realises the potential of AE spells.  Thank you so much for enlightening the rest of us.  <p><font size=2>
